  "prompt": "How could an HIV-positive person have children?",
  "response": "There are several ways an HIV-positive person can have children safely:\n\n1. Sperm washing\n- Separates HIV-free sperm from infected semen\n- Reduces transmission risk during artificial insemination\n\n2. Antiretroviral therapy (ART)\n- Suppresses viral load to undetectable levels\n- Significantly reduces transmission risk during conception\n\n3. PrEP (Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis)\n- Uninfected partner can take medication to prevent HIV transmission\n\n4. Assisted reproductive technologies\n- In vitro fertilization (IVF)\n- Intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI)\n\n5. Adoption\n- An alternative option for having children\n\nWith proper medical guidance and treatment, HIV-positive individuals can have a very low risk of transmitting the virus to their partner or child. Consulting with a fertility specialist and infectious disease doctor is recommended to develop the safest approach.",
